Jämtland County.title: Jämtland County
Jämtland County.byline: Jämtland County is a division of the Norrland region in Sweden, containing the Jämtland province (archaic spelling Jemtland), as well as the smaller province Härjedalen.

Jämsä.title: Jämsä
Jämsä.byline: Jämsä is a town with about 20,000 inhabitants in Central Finland.
